        <span class="a11y">Credit: </span>
        Zaydee Sanchez for ProPublica
    </span>
    
    
    </figcaption>

        </figure>
            <div class="opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper ">

                    <span class="opener__topics ">
            <a class="opener__topics-link " href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/immigration">Immigration</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed " >        He Died Building a Ship for the U.S. Government. His Family Got Nothing.
    </h1>

    <h2 class="opener__dek " style="display: none" >        Elmer Pérez was one of many immigrants hired by U.S. shipbuilders to fill the urgent need for skilled labor. These workers do the same jobs and take the same risks as their American counterparts, but are left on their own when things go wrong.
    </h2>
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--left     " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/nicole-foy">Nicole Foy</a>    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-10-22EDT05:00">Oct. 22, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
    </time>

    <div class="article-meta-1__section-actions
            " data-pp-location="article story-tools">
