        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://projects.propublica.org/new-effects-of-immigration">
                                    What the Data Reveals About U.S. Immigration Ahead of the 2024 Election
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Recent years have seen a big increase in migrants crossing the U.S. border. But that’s not the most significant change. It’s that many are coming from new countries and with more legal ways to be here. All this is shaping the 2024 election.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mica-rosenberg">Mica Rosenberg</a> and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/jeff-ernsthausen">Jeff Ernsthausen</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-10-21EDT05:00">Oct. 21, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

